Author: Rodrigo Moraes
email: rdcmdev@gmail.com

Developed on: Linux x86 64 Ubuntu 16.04 kernel 4.4.0-31

Requirements:
    1. OpenCV 2.4.13
    2. Cmake 3.5.1
    3. GNU Make 4.1
    4. g++ 5.4.0
    5. C++ version 17
    6. cpplint 1.3.0(install from pip)

Integrated Development Environmet: 
    Name: Visual Studio Code 1.19.1(Optional)
    Extensions:
        1. C++ integration - C/C++ for Visual Studio Code
        2. Cmake snippets - CMake For VisualStudio Code
        3. Keyboard Shortcuts - IntelliJ IDEA Key Bindings for Visual Studio Code
        4. Embedded terminal - VSC Open in Terminal
        5. Autocomplete folder - Path Intellisense
        6. Lint c++ - cpplint
        7. Icons - vscode-icons
        8. Theme - Dark+ (default dark)
    Json setting:
        {
            "workbench.colorTheme": "Default Dark+",
            "workbench.iconTheme": "vscode-icons",
            "editor.fontSize": 14,
            "explorer.confirmDelete": false,
            "explorer.confirmDragAndDrop": false,
            "C_Cpp.clang_format_fallbackStyle": "Google",
            "editor.tabSize": 2
        }

Cmake usage:
    1. Go to folder build
    2. Inside of it execute this comand below:
        cmake ..

GNU Make usage:
    1. Go to folder build
    2. Inside of it execute this comand below:
        make

Git commit style: https://udacity.github.io/git-styleguide/

Google C++ format: https://google.github.io/styleguide/cppguide.html

All project executable(binaries) are on folder bin at root of this project 

Help links to install OpenCV
    https://www.learnopencv.com/install-opencv3-on-ubuntu/
    https://github.com/GaoHongchen/DIPDemoQt5/issues/1
    https://docs.opencv.org/master/d7/d9f/tutorial_linux_install.html